  <h2>Favorite Senior Portrait Locations in Fenton</h2>

  <h3>Dibbleville &amp; Downtown Fenton</h3>
  <p>The historic Dibbleville district has character that you can't fake — old brick, interesting textures, and great light filtering through the tree-lined streets. It's walkable, relaxed, and gives us an editorial urban vibe without driving to a big city.</p>

  <h3>Fenton Mill Pond</h3>
  <p>The Mill Pond is Fenton's centerpiece for a reason. Water reflections, the walking bridge, and green space all in one compact spot. At sunset, the light reflecting off the water creates this warm glow that's absolutely perfect for portraits.</p>

  <h3>Linden County Park</h3>
  <p>Just minutes from Fenton, Linden County Park gives us open fields, mature trees, and that quiet natural beauty that makes Michigan fall sessions so special. The variety here means we can get multiple distinct looks without driving between locations.</p>

  <h3>Silver Lake &amp; Lake Fenton Area</h3>
  <p>If you want a lakeside session, the beaches and shore areas around Silver Lake and Lake Fenton are gorgeous at golden hour. Water, sky, sand — simple and stunning.</p>

  <h2>What Your Session Looks Like</h2>
  <p>Every session starts with a consultation where we plan outfits, locations, and timing. On session day, I guide you through everything — natural poses, relaxed expressions, real moments. Most sessions include 2-3 outfit changes and last about 90 minutes. You'll receive your private gallery within 2-3 weeks.</p>

